node.text: Shout out to the bus drivers and their cashiers for letting me on the buses even though they are full and aren’t letting anymore people on 😂👌🏻. Well, not the first bus. He completely kept on going and I ended up waiting almost an hour to get a ride getting bit by mosquitoes lol🙄. But, the other drivers have been very kind and always let me on hehe. Here in Skiathos I chose not to rent a car, instead I chose to use the buses. The buses connect you to the whole island and there is one main road so it’s fairly easy. The only problem is during peak season they are very crowded and get overly full at the end and beginning stops (the end stop is one of the most popular and crowded beaches and the beginning stop is the town); so anyone in between is out of luck lol. They are supposed to run every 20 min but sometimes it’s every 30. Anyway, me and the bus drivers are buddies now and once they realize it’s me they stop even though they weren’t going to initially 😂👌🏻. ευχαριστώ #greekislands #skiathos #travel

node.text: Not many people know about this beautiful island. It’s not as popular as Santorini and Mykonos, but the lack of popularity doesn’t mean it lacks beauty. Third time here and honestly I think it deserves more praise 😍👌🏻🙌🏻 #greece #greecetravel #greekislands #skiathos

node.text:
This was my last day in Cyprus, and although the water was beautiful, the sun and the heat was almost unbearable. When I was there the temperature was about 90 with a heat index of 104, humidity about 70 percent and a UV index of 10! Lol. Needless to say I definitely got a few shades darker and I wasn’t even laying out 😂. The water though was refreshingly cold, and I mean cold lol. But, after 10 min in that heat you definitely welcome that cold dip. Regardless, I’m Happy I was able to cross off this beautiful destination off my bucket list, but if I was to again I would probably go early spring or fall 😂👌🏻. Are you traveling anywhere this summer? 😀
_
Bikini @amiclubwear
